JOHANNESBURG – The Pietermaritzburg High Court on Monday sentenced Thabani Osborne Shange to a maximum of 30- years imprisonment for six counts of murder and attempted murder. Shange was one of a group of five people that attacked and killed a family in Georgedale area, Hammersdale earlier this year. The KwaZulu-Natal Acting Provincial Commissioner, Major General Bheki Langa welcome the sentence. READ: Six shot dead execution style in KZN “We hope this sentence will bring closure to the family who lost their loved ones in a brutal manner. This sentence will serve as a warning to other criminals that you cannot evade the long arm of the Law,” he said. READ: KZN family murders have police stumped His accomplice Sisenda Mvinjana was also sentenced to 30-years in March this year. Three suspects are still at large and police are investigating.  eNCA